---
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Welcome to Astro.">
	<main>
		<!-- Navbar -->
		<div class="w-full px-3">
			<nav class="max-w-2xl justify-between mx-auto flex py-3">
				<a href="/">
					<img
						width="145"
						height="40"
						src="/glendaily-logo.svg"
						alt="Glendaily Logo"
					/>
				</a>
			</nav>
		</div>

		<!-- Hero -->
		<div class="my-6 w-full px-3">
			<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-3">
				<h1 class="text-white text-6xl font-bold">Glendale Acosta</h1>
				<ul
					class="text-lg my-2 text-gray-300 flex flex-col md:gap-6 md:flex-row"
				>
					<li class="my-1">💻 Frontend Engineer</li>
					<li class="my-1">💼 Entrepreneur</li>
					<li class="my-1">🏙️ San Francisco, CA</li>
				</ul>

				<h1 class="text-white mt-10 mb-6 text-xl font-bold">
					I'm a frontend engineer and I truly love what I do.
				</h1>
				<p class="text-gray-300 my-6 text-xl">
					I've spent the past year working on my own SaaS products and
					while I've learned an enormous amount about building large
					applications, I've also learned that I hate working on
					projects alone 😢
				</p>
				<p class="text-gray-300 my-6 text-xl"></p>

				<h1 class="text-white mt-10 text-3xl font-bold">
					Experience
					<span class="text-lg font-normal text-gray-400"
						>(3 years)</span
					>
				</h1>

				<div class="my-4">
					<Card
						title="Short Story Box"
						body={`
							I was the only frontend engineer and was responsible for making architectural descisions on for the UI.
							It was an insanely fast-paced and cutthroat environment with regular 10-12 hours per day.
							Despite the difficult workplace, I thrived and delivered every single week by quickly scoping out projects,
							designing myself in Figma, and shipping extremely fast.
						`}
						href="/"
						tldr={[
							"Only Frontend Engineer responsible for UI architectural decisions, but also designed and worked on the backend.",
							"15% of time designing in Figma",
							"60% of time in Next.js Frontend",
							"35% of time in Python Backend",
							"Worked 10-12 hours per day in a fast environment",
							"Cool Projects – I basically built typeform :)",
						]}
						tech={[
							"Typescript",
							"React",
							"TailwindCSS",
							"HTML & CSS",
							"Next.js",
							"Python",
							"Postgres",
							"Figma",
						]}
					/>
				</div>

				<div class="my-4">
					<Card
						title="SentinelOne"
						body={`
							I was a frontend engineer on a large team of 10+ engineers. I worked on Scalyr, which
							was a log observability tool. My first project was building out our alert system and
							then I was quickly promoted and mainly worked on the dashboard page.
						`}
						href="/"
						tldr={["I'll fill this out later"]}
						tech={[
							"Typescript",
							"JavaScript",
							"React",
							"HTML & CSS/SASS",
							"Recoil",
							"Cypress",
							"Jest",
						]}
					/>
				</div>

				<div class="my-4">
					<Card
						title="Humble Dot"
						body={`
							I was a frontend engineer on a large team of 10+ engineers. I worked on Scalyr, which
							was a log observability tool. My first project was building out our alert system and
							then I was quickly promoted and mainly worked on the dashboard page.
						`}
						href="/"
						tldr={["I'll fill this out later"]}
						tech={[
							"JavaScript",
							"React",
							"HTML & CSS/SASS",
							"Styled Components",
							"Jest",
						]}
					/>
				</div>

				<!-- <div class="my-4">
					<Card title="My Entrepreneur Phase" body="foo" href="/">
						<div>TLDR</div>
						<ul>
							<li>
								Only Frontend Engineer responsible for
								architectural decisions
							</li>
						</ul>
					</Card>
				</div>

				<div class="my-4">
					<Card title="Sentinel One" body="foo" href="/" />
				</div>

				<div class="my-4">
					<Card title="Humble Dot" body="foo" href="/" />
				</div> -->
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
